==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pigskin
<hw>Pig"skin`</hw> <pr>(p⟦icr⟧g"sk⟦icr⟧n`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The skin of a pig, -- used chiefly for making saddles;
hence, a colloquial or slang term for a saddle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A football; -- so called because the covering is
often made of pigskin.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pigsney</ent>⟦br⟧
